    <div class="content-wrapper">

      <div class="box">
        <h1>Admissions</h1>
        <p>
          Specialist Technical College welcomes applications from learners who
          are motivated to develop their technical and professional skills within
          a British-style college environment in Kosovo.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page provides a general overview of how to apply. Prospective
          learners are encouraged to contact the college for individual advice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Entry Requirements</h2>
        <p>
          Entry requirements vary by programme and level, but may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Completion of compulsory schooling or equivalent for entry to Level 3 programmes.</li>
          <li>Evidence of suitable prior study or experience for Levels 4 and 5.</li>
          <li>Basic competency in English, sufficient to engage with teaching and assessment.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Detailed entry requirements for each programme are available from the
          Admissions team.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>How to Apply</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Review the information on the relevant subject page (e.g. Computing &amp; IT).</li>
          <li>Contact the college to discuss your goals and suitability for the programme.</li>
          <li>Complete an application form (available as a PDF or from the Admissions team).</li>
          <li>Submit supporting documents as requested (e.g. certificates, ID).</li>
          <li>Attend an interview or guidance meeting if required.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Fees and Payment</h2>
        <p>
          Programme fees are published on the relevant subject pages where
          applicable. For example, Computing &amp; IT currently lists:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Level 3 Computing &amp; IT – €600 per academic year</li>
          <li>Level 4 Computing &amp; IT – €1,400 per academic year</li>
          <li>Level 5 Computing &amp; IT – €1,400 per academic year</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Information about payment schedules and any additional costs (such as
          materials) is available from the Admissions team.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Advice and Guidance</h2>
        <p>
          Choosing the right level and pathway is important. The college offers
          information, advice and guidance to help applicants select an
          appropriate course and to understand progression opportunities.
        </p>
        <p>
          To arrange a guidance conversation, please contact:
          <br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@specialist.college">info@specialist.college</a>
        </p>
      </div>

